			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Ok, JIm is aware of the lev 20 Body root. And he DID want to give us an AE, but not certain if/when that can happen. Admittedly we got a huge boost overall even if no other changes are made.
<br />

<br />
But the one people might not like. It is way too easy to hit 100% mez resist. It was intended to be possible, but not really a gurantee. We can hit over 60% resists at various times, with various combinations, so even the 3rd spell in the line can potentially grant full immunity. Normally it is fiarly easy to hit 26%, and with a few other exttra factors hit immunity with the second one. This was never intedned to be so easy. So expect the Mez resist levels to drop some. You will likely still be able to make yourself immune, but it will most likely require the highest spell and complete dedication to do it.
<br />

<br />
Now my reccommendation, which may or may not be used, was to drop the self buff, but then let the group pulse stack. This woudl let us still get up to those levels if we dedicated spec for it, and resist gear, and give us more incentive to run this spell to aid our groups. I don't know where it is going, but as it sits right now it is a bit much. And if other classes may see this ability also in the future, I don't mind it being made a bit more difficult to get complete immunity.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
