				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Thnaks for the update i3ullseye, but with the information in the grab bag regarding resists lets face it sorcs are screwed.
<br />

<br />
If we spec high in mind we might as well just toss all the spare points in the bin. A lvl 20 AE root will stick on no one.
<br />

<br />
A mind sorc is a one trick pony. If  someone else has already cast mezz you might as well sit on your arse.
<br />

<br />
Even if the root was ae it would do more harm than good.
<br />

<br />
There is a group of mezzed mids. 30 secs have past and there is about 10 secs of your long duration lvl 44 mezz ( bah lvl 44 with it’s in built resist factor)  left. You cast your lvl 20 ae root. Resist resist resist. Congratulations you have just broken the mezz and accomplished nothing.
<br />

<br />
If a sorc goes for a balanced spec, resist rates on mezz and root are massive. Our nuke is lvl 35, can you say resist.
<br />

<br />
The only way to spec a sorc is to completely gimp yourself.
<br />

<br />
No point making a body sorc. Make a wizard
<br />

<br />
No point making a matter sorc. Make a cabbie.
<br />

<br />
Make a mind sorc and you are now the ultimate group dependant support class. 
<br />

<br />
I wish mythic had never told us this. I was happy in my ignorance.
<br />

<br />
You’ll notice I didn’t even moan about the sorc nerf of the sorc buff. Truth is I don’t care anymore.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
